Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.99,0:00:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This convention program will be translated
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.50,0:00:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,into more than 450 languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.63,0:00:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This work is supported\Nby branch offices around the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.01,0:00:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of us has\Nan opportunity to show appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.22,0:00:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,for the spiritual blessings\Nwe have received in our own language.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.68,0:00:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,One way we can do this\Nis by making voluntary gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.23,0:00:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in accord with our circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.98,0:00:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Donations can be made online
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.44,0:00:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at donate.jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.49,0:00:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether young or old, we face tests of faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.78,0:00:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Changing circumstances\Ncan bring new challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.79,0:01:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we meet\Neach test with unwavering faith?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.17,0:01:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We invite you to put yourself in the scene
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.00,0:01:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as you watch the drama
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.01,0:01:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Daniel: A Lifetime of Faith—Part I.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.08,0:01:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My king.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.00,0:01:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,General.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.63,0:01:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve starved them out,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.17,0:01:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehoiachin still refuses to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.75,0:01:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Negotiations don’t concern me, General,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:01:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but your incompetence does.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.59,0:01:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Finish it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.26,0:02:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or you’ll not find me as forgiving as the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.52,0:02:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, my king.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.95,0:02:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what Jehovah of armies says,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.29,0:02:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Because you did not obey my words,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.66,0:02:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‘all this land will be reduced to ruins,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.54,0:02:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and this land and its inhabitants
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘will have to serve the king of Babylon
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.71,0:02:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for 70 years.’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.10,0:02:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.31,0:02:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.85,0:02:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s almost sundown!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.14,0:02:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Jeremiah was speaking today, and I, uh
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.56,0:02:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,—I stopped by the temple on the way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.32,0:02:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re almost ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.37,0:03:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You were at the temple again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.38,0:03:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.55,0:03:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“To gaze upon the pleasantness of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.92,0:03:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and to look with appreciation upon his temple.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.89,0:03:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I have something for you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.78,0:03:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can always have Jehovah’s words with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.07,0:03:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.50,0:03:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.54,0:03:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s going to happen to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.26,0:03:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What always happens to Jehovah’s faithful servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.51,0:04:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Have no fear, Jehovah is our shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.14,0:04:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinner’s ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.07,0:04:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see our old neighbor at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.16,0:04:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn’t see him at all today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.79,0:04:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.79,0:04:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw our neighbor Eli the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.79,0:04:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Eli is always getting into trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.38,0:04:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s sing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.38,0:04:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Son, pick a psalm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.89,0:04:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is my light and my salvation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.51,0:04:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You always choose that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hushim.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.56,0:04:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is my light
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.78,0:04:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“and my salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.65,0:05:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Whom should I fear?”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.95,0:05:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.33,0:05:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay and play?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.20,0:05:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to go with Papa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.21,0:05:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,When you come back, do you want to play Noah’s ark?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.21,0:05:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:05:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And who will you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.59,0:05:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll be a lion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.67,0:06:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I’ll be an elephant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.27,0:06:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehoiachin has surrendered!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.32,0:06:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehoiachin has surrendered!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.36,0:06:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Household of Eber, tribe of Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.44,0:06:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,open up at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.99,0:06:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you outside! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.61,0:06:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s happened. They’re here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.62,0:06:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather your things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.16,0:06:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.20,0:06:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.08,0:06:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.67,0:06:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t live here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.55,0:06:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hushim, grab our bags.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.82,0:08:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate this place!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.70,0:08:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.73,0:09:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Open up! 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.07,0:09:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All four—outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Check the back room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.83,0:09:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,By the order of the king, you are coming with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.54,0:09:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, of the tribe of Judah—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You will receive training
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.59,0:09:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in the house of the great King Nebuchadnezzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.93,0:09:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.22,0:09:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Princes and nobles belong in the palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.44,0:09:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s not a prince; he’s just a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.78,0:09:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I will go if it’s a servant you seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.20,0:09:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I’m taking the boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.03,0:09:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.25,0:10:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we say goodbye?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.13,0:10:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Make it quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.48,0:10:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong, my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.73,0:10:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.26,0:11:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.72,0:11:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishael.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.68,0:11:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.89,0:11:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn’t think we’d let you come here alone, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.89,0:11:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Azariah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.85,0:11:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hananiah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.10,0:11:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Chislon and Ahitub.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.85,0:11:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.85,0:11:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.03,0:11:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.99,0:11:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The palace, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.82,0:12:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So like Joseph in Pharaoh’s house?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, like Joseph in the dungeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.16,0:12:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn’t seem so bad to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.87,0:12:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.17,0:12:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chislon, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t say something, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.38,0:12:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.42,0:12:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.63,0:12:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back again sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the Jewish boys that Ashpenaz summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.29,0:13:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been chosen
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.29,0:13:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,because you are wise,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.55,0:13:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but you are lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.09,0:13:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You will learn our writing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.30,0:13:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and our language.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.81,0:13:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be given new names,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.19,0:13:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the end of three years,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you will serve the great King Nebuchadnezzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.36,0:14:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Today,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.37,0:14:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,you are foreigners
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.50,0:14:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,—tomorrow, the gods willing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.67,0:14:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Babylonians.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.04,0:15:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Meshach.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like a Meshach.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.22,0:15:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Our new names sound like their gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.43,0:15:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,New names, new language—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.14,0:15:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon they’ll want us to worship their gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.14,0:15:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.14,0:15:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My father had idols, and he worshipped Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.11,0:15:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see the same city I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.78,0:15:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s the center of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.40,0:15:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll even eat from the king’s table.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.95,0:15:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What do Babylonians eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.79,0:15:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,His servants are given only the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.55,0:15:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t eat from this food.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.06,0:15:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you making a big deal out of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.14,0:15:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it’s unclean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.56,0:15:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.52,0:16:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Our, uh, our God
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.82,0:16:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn’t allow us to eat such foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.07,0:16:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You fear your God?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.66,0:16:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.25,0:16:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I am afraid of my lord the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.71,0:16:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who has assigned your food and drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He insists on these selections
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.88,0:16:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to maintain your strength and vitality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What if he should see you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.85,0:16:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,looking worse in appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.73,0:16:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,than the other youths?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.77,0:16:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You would make me guilty before the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.19,0:16:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I must obey the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.45,0:16:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So must you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,—all of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.58,0:17:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When dinner is served, I expect you to be hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.61,0:17:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t speak for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.03,0:17:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.74,0:17:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make your own choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.78,0:17:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn’t you hear him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.87,0:17:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a new land with new laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.21,0:17:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So what if some of the food is unbled?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.88,0:17:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just food!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.26,0:17:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah commanded us not to eat blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.18,0:17:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s your interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.93,0:17:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must not eat . . . any blood at all.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.85,0:18:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s to interpret in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.98,0:18:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should all take a moment and pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.52,0:18:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.36,0:18:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.61,0:18:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is in Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.28,0:18:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re in Babylon now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.70,0:18:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you believe that Jehovah is here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.16,0:18:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah said that we’re his witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.25,0:18:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What will people say about Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.42,0:18:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,if we give in and break his laws?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.51,0:18:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Your meal is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.78,0:18:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.20,0:19:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.66,0:19:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we eat those foods, we’ll disobey our God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.25,0:19:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to starve?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.21,0:19:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, of course not,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but He forbids us from eating blood
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.88,0:19:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and food that he calls “unclean.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.38,0:19:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, test your servants for ten days,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and let us be given some vegetables to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.97,0:19:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and water to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.02,0:19:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Just give us ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then deal with your servants
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.28,0:19:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,according to what you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.38,0:19:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.89,0:20:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go, thanks to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.28,0:20:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to try this meat. It’s amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.75,0:20:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen anything like this before?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.26,0:22:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.26,0:22:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Oh, wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.72,0:22:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.86,0:22:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashpenaz has summoned you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.34,0:22:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, these young men are of royal . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.72,0:22:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.02,0:22:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve been watching you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.90,0:23:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,—all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.57,0:23:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t bow to our idols,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.08,0:23:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you pray only to your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.29,0:23:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and you are not eating our foods.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.88,0:23:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They insisted that their God would not . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.09,0:23:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.63,0:23:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you look healthier than the others. 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.76,0:23:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue giving them the diet they’ve requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.65,0:23:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And Belteshazzar,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.78,0:23:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,your future is bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.79,0:23:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t waste it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.72,0:24:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring in the next group.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.32,0:24:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The total rations would be fifteen {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}kurru,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.95,0:24:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,two {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}p{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}ān{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}u,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.41,0:24:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and five {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}s{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}ūtu.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.41,0:24:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.96,0:24:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How much interest
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.96,0:24:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,may a merchant charge on money and grain?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.55,0:24:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be 40 percent, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.09,0:24:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty percent?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.22,0:24:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you learned only to be a thief
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.60,0:24:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the past three years?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.35,0:24:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And you, Meshach?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.43,0:25:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate is 20 percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.10,0:25:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.28,0:25:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Which star of Enlil is brightest
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.53,0:25:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Urgula constellation?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.67,0:25:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.96,0:25:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the Lugal star.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.34,0:25:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.05,0:25:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a tower that is high
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.18,0:25:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but, nonetheless, has no shade.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.22,0:25:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.14,0:25:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ziggurat?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.19,0:25:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.99,0:25:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can solve the riddle?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.70,0:25:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It is sunlight, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.49,0:25:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.58,0:26:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,My wise men teach that the gods
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.33,0:26:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,are responsible for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.46,0:26:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If that’s so,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.46,0:26:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,why do the good suffer and the evil prosper?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.67,0:26:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has been able to answer . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.69,0:26:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,As you say, O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.69,0:26:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,‘the wise do not always have the food,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.73,0:26:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‘nor do the intelligent always have the riches,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.24,0:26:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,‘nor do those with knowledge always have success,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.86,0:26:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,‘because time and unexpected events
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.24,0:26:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,overtake them all.’
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.37,0:26:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Who wrote those words?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.00,0:26:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Solomon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.92,0:26:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Famed for his wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.67,0:26:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But its source was his God,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.59,0:26:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,our God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.18,0:27:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Take them away.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.69,0:27:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When should we return?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.27,0:27:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You won’t!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.73,0:27:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to your families.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.69,0:27:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve proven worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.61,0:27:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Belteshazzar, no—not the four of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.91,0:27:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We have more to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.63,0:27:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.63,0:27:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but you’ve proven to be ten times better
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.80,0:27:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,than any priest or conjurer that I’ve met.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.10,0:27:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashpenaz will arrange
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.68,0:27:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for you to serve in the palace with my wise men.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.69,0:27:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe your gifts were wasted in Jerusalem,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.69,0:27:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but here they will be put to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.84,0:28:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The victory in Jerusalem is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.51,0:28:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our forces are now preparing to besiege Tyre.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.68,0:28:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They should remember what happened to Zedekiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.39,0:28:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods are with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.95,0:28:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerah,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.20,0:28:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.87,0:28:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s about Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.69,0:29:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.31,0:29:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To see my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.92,0:29:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, we’ve had to make do.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.56,0:29:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.17,0:30:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.81,0:30:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.89,0:30:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.11,0:30:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They tore down the walls;
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.49,0:30:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,they torched its towers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.08,0:30:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Many died.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.71,0:30:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And they burned down Jehovah’s house!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.72,0:31:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn’t our people listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.60,0:31:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they think Jehovah couldn’t see
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.39,0:31:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what they were doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.02,0:31:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as our temple existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.02,0:31:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,our people had hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.57,0:31:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as Jehovah exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.66,0:31:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we have hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.28,0:31:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But he’s rejected us
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.37,0:31:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,because of our unrighteousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.79,0:31:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn’t
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.00,0:31:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—not everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.17,0:31:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah told Ezekiel
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.97,0:31:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that in his eyes you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.47,0:31:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,are as righteous as Noah
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.39,0:31:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and Job.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.31,0:32:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.19,0:32:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He did.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.78,0:32:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah cares so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.00,0:32:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,then why are we in exile? 
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.88,0:32:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can’t we go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.13,0:32:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why can’t we be together?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.43,0:32:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You are home, Son.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.53,0:32:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t have all the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.16,0:32:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay close to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.79,0:33:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.47,0:33:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.35,0:34:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.06,0:34:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’m agitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.48,0:34:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to know what I dreamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.48,0:34:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.48,0:34:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Relate the dream to your servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.82,0:34:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We will tell the interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.36,0:34:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.74,0:34:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don’t make the dream known to me
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.36,0:34:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the interpretation,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.37,0:34:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll be dismembered,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.99,0:34:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and your houses will be turned into public latrines.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.08,0:34:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you do tell me the dream
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.04,0:34:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and the interpretation,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.04,0:34:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you will receive gifts and a reward
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.59,0:34:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and great honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.67,0:34:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve got to buy some time
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.80,0:34:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can consult the spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.89,0:34:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The scrolls will tell you what the dreams say.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.89,0:34:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to come up with a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.60,0:34:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants us to tell him the dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.85,0:34:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.85,0:34:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has ever asked this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.02,0:34:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.02,0:34:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.02,0:34:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can buy us some time,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.19,0:34:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we can consult the spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.28,0:34:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve agreed to tell me something false
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.53,0:34:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and deceitful until the situation changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.66,0:34:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Deceitful?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.12,0:34:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Deceitful!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.08,0:35:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is not a man on earth
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.08,0:35:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,who can do what the king demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.16,0:35:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What the king is asking is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.87,0:35:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No one exists who could tell this to the king except
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.46,0:35:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—except the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.56,0:35:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Arioch,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.52,0:35:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,seize them!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.52,0:35:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Down!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.15,0:35:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Down!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.61,0:35:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.02,0:35:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.19,0:35:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.28,0:35:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.74,0:35:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By the order of the king, round them up!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.62,0:35:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.62,0:35:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.70,0:35:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.58,0:35:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t hear everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.41,0:35:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but the wise men angered the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.16,0:35:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is to be executed by dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.83,0:35:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.67,0:35:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll try to learn more.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.76,0:36:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes—Chaldean, Egyptian, Jewish
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.30,0:36:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,—all the wise men.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.56,0:36:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Arioch?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.81,0:36:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Belteshazzar, you shouldn’t be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.15,0:36:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is there such a harsh order from the king?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.73,0:36:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.78,0:36:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one can tell him what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.78,0:36:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Flee now!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.78,0:36:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you escape before dawn, you might survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.01,0:36:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me why I asked for them
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.55,0:36:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and you haven’t brought them?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.55,0:36:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren’t the gods talking to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.97,0:36:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them and all of their families brought here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.27,0:36:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to look into the whites of their eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.52,0:36:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask them why.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.66,0:37:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang them without their skins!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.87,0:37:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the gods look down on their flesh,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.21,0:37:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and then throw their bodies in the Euphrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.58,0:37:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashpenaz.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.63,0:37:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What good are wise men without wisdom?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.67,0:37:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.22,0:37:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to speak with the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.55,0:37:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.14,0:37:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, let me speak with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.89,0:37:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, this is Belteshazzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.94,0:37:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.61,0:37:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,interpretations belong to my God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.78,0:37:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows your dream and what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.74,0:37:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, where is your God? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.54,0:37:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that he—
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.04,0:37:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that he will reveal it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.21,0:37:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, give me time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.89,0:38:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We have until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.35,0:38:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To do what?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.47,0:38:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,To reveal the dream to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.98,0:38:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how much of the dream
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.40,0:38:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has Jehovah revealed to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.28,0:38:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, nothing yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.07,0:38:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah revealed
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.62,0:38:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would interpret it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.21,0:38:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Not exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.75,0:38:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.75,0:38:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you know this is even going to happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.25,0:38:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I can’t be sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.30,0:38:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d better be sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.76,0:38:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.84,0:38:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If he reveals the dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.18,0:38:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it proves that he’s the true God!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.35,0:38:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.36,0:39:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.36,0:39:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.41,0:39:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray that Jehovah have mercy on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.79,0:39:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.01,0:39:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,surely you didn’t bring us here just to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.76,0:39:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What will people say?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.89,0:39:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We told them that you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.89,0:39:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are the God of the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.48,0:39:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the only God who can reveal secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.69,0:39:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.48,0:39:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,vindicate yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.20,0:40:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerah!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.42,0:40:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I have found a man from the exiles of Judah
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.93,0:40:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,who can make known the interpretation to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.64,0:40:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I know who he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.85,0:40:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really make known to me
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.81,0:40:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the dream that I saw
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.14,0:41:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.07,0:41:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a God in the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.08,0:41:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who is a Revealer of secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.91,0:41:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has made known to King Nebuchadnezzar
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.75,0:41:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what is to happen in the final part of the days.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.80,0:41:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your dream:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.15,0:41:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw an immense image.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.04,0:42:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That image was standing in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.96,0:42:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You yourself are the head of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.76,0:42:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But after you another kingdom will rise,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.80,0:42:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,inferior to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.18,0:42:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then another kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.43,0:42:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a third one, of copper,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.81,0:42:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that will rule over the whole earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.90,0:42:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the fourth kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.48,0:42:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it will be strong like iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.61,0:42:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The kingdom will be divided.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.24,0:42:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the toes of the feet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.41,0:42:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,were partly of iron and partly of clay,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.79,0:42:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so the kingdom will be partly strong
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.08,0:42:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and partly fragile.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.54,0:42:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In the days of those kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.54,0:42:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.55,0:42:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,will set up a kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.01,0:42:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that will never be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.01,0:42:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And this kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.01,0:42:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,will not be passed on to any other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.57,0:43:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It will crush and put an end
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.57,0:43:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to all these kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.90,0:43:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And it alone will stand forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.57,0:44:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The dream is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.87,0:44:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation is trustworthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.49,0:44:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.99,0:44:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring a fine robe
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.70,0:44:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and a necklace of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.71,0:44:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Burn incense before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.56,0:45:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly your God is a God of gods
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.78,0:45:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Lord of kings
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.82,0:45:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Revealer of secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.53,0:45:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,May your God be honored
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.53,0:45:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,by the honor I give you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.79,0:45:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You are now ruler over all the province of Babylon.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.30,0:45:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, these servants
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.72,0:45:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,also worship the God in the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.47,0:45:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,May they too be appointed to administer the province?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.73,0:45:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Make the necessary arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.69,0:45:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You have proven far superior
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.69,0:46:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,than these so-called wise men.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.28,0:46:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I now appoint you their chief prefect.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.75,0:46:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear Nebuchadnezzar?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.75,0:46:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,When he said, “Your God is a God of gods
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.17,0:46:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and a Lord of kings.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.72,0:46:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered your prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.47,0:46:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered our prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.78,0:46:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s going to happen next?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.99,0:46:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we go back to Jerusalem?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.08,0:46:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know what happens next,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.08,0:46:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but as long as we stay close to Jehovah . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.04,0:46:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He will always be with us
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.05,0:47:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as we have faith in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.43,0:47:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing in the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.47,0:47:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,about kingdoms crushing kingdoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.47,0:47:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.61,0:47:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.27,0:47:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But how did he know the dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.32,0:47:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Amar-Utu!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.28,0:47:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Amar-Utu, what message from the gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.62,0:47:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I have examined a sheep’s liver.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.16,0:47:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your future is bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.70,0:47:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The stars of Shabatu, the giant,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.37,0:47:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,speak only of your grandeur.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.71,0:47:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’m the head of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.71,0:47:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah said so.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.08,0:47:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Your dream revealed many good things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.00,0:47:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But this Belteshazzar, he’s a Jew—
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.46,0:47:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s a clever Jew, to be sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.47,0:47:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but he couldn’t interpret dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.47,0:47:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,before he came to Babylon.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.05,0:47:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He first had to be educated here
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.68,0:47:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and given a Babylonian name,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.56,0:47:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a name that honors our great god Bel.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.48,0:48:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Bel used this young captive
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.48,0:48:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to reveal great things to you—
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.11,0:48:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Bel,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.53,0:48:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,not Jehovah, who you defeated in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.10,0:48:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So the tree is my enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.31,0:48:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it after the seven times pass over?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.23,0:48:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it is you again, O great king.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.53,0:48:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You are fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.16,0:48:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At last—
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.25,0:49:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Belteshazzar, chief of the magic-practicing priests,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.17,0:49:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,all of the other wise men are unable
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.50,0:49:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the interpretation known to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.09,0:49:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are able to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.47,0:49:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain to me the visions I’ve seen in my dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.90,0:49:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.86,0:49:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a tree in the midst of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.37,0:49:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and its height, it was enormous
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.79,0:49:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—it was enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.08,0:49:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the tree grew and became strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.71,0:49:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and its top—
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.71,0:49:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And its top reached the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.34,0:49:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,reached the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.55,0:49:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tree grew and became strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.68,0:49:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . holy one . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.72,0:49:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chop down the tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.51,0:49:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And I saw a watcher . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.68,0:49:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Chop down the tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.27,0:49:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . with a banding of iron
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.98,0:50:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and of copper.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.82,0:50:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So who’s the tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.05,0:50:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,O my lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.35,0:50:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,may the dream apply to those hating you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.52,0:50:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and its interpretation to your enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.23,0:50:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The tree that you saw
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.36,0:50:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that grew great and became strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.48,0:50:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,whose top reached the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.36,0:50:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and was visible to all the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.91,0:50:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,which had beautiful foliage, abundant fruit,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.87,0:50:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and food for all,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.16,0:51:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,beneath which the beasts of the field would dwell
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.50,0:51:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and on whose branches
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.50,0:51:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the birds of the heavens would reside,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.92,0:51:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it is you, O king.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.05,0:51:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the king saw a watcher, a holy one,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.09,0:51:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,coming down from the heavens who was saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.26,0:51:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“Chop down the tree and destroy it,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.79,0:51:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“but leave the stump with its roots in the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.83,0:51:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“with a banding of iron and of copper.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.00,0:51:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“And let the dew of the heavens make it wet,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.25,0:51:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“and let its portion be
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.26,0:51:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the beasts of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.09,0:51:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,until seven times pass over it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.97,0:52:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the interpretation, O king;
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.97,0:52:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it is the decree of the Most High.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.19,0:52:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be driven away from among men,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.31,0:52:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and your dwelling will be with the beasts of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.32,0:52:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will be given vegetation to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.90,0:52:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,just like bulls,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.57,0:52:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will become wet
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.28,0:52:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,with the dew of the heavens,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.45,0:52:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and seven times will pass over you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.66,0:52:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,until you know
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.75,0:52:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that the Most High is Ruler
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.79,0:52:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the kingdom of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.88,0:52:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he grants it to whomever he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.59,0:52:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But because they said to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.59,0:52:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the stump of the tree with its roots,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.84,0:52:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,your kingdom will be yours again
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.01,0:52:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,after you come to know
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.18,0:52:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that the heavens are ruling.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.77,0:52:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn away from your sins
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.15,0:52:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,by doing what is right
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.27,0:52:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and from your iniquity
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.57,0:52:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,by showing mercy to the poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.90,0:53:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be that your prosperity will be extended.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.05,0:53:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Belteshazzar know when this will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.72,0:53:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.26,0:53:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But your wise men
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.26,0:53:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,doubt that his interpretation can be trusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.10,0:53:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the facts:
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.73,0:53:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Egypt’s gods told the Egyptians
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.73,0:53:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that they would defeat us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.61,0:53:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, you destroyed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.37,0:53:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So why should the God of the Jews
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.04,0:53:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,be given any more credit?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.62,0:53:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at what you’ve done.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.50,0:53:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The gods are with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.30,0:54:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You have made Babylon
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.42,0:54:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest kingdom on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.39,0:54:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Belteshazzar wants you to grovel like a slave
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.31,0:54:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.39,0:54:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A strong king means a strong kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.73,0:54:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us continue with our discussion
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.98,0:54:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the stars of Enlil.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.53,0:54:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the Lugal star is the brightest star
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.24,0:54:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Urgula constellation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.91,0:54:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The stars are reliable,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.41,0:54:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,unlike the gods of defeated nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.54,0:54:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back to Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.21,0:54:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you could
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.96,0:54:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if there was anything left of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.94,0:54:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Has Jehovah revealed anything new?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.02,0:55:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been ten months
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.03,0:55:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and still no sign of this supposed insanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.99,0:55:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.66,0:55:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, as we do when we read the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.54,0:55:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But we still shape the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.58,0:55:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be held responsible for the words,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.71,0:55:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and when a wise man speaks lies, well . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.46,0:55:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I spoke only what Jehovah revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.76,0:55:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.68,0:55:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,when some couldn’t interpret the dream image?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.31,0:55:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,A death sentence followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.14,0:55:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was a flattering interpretation,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.02,0:55:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that the king was a head of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.81,0:55:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, you’ve said he’ll go mad,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.48,0:55:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.78,0:55:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.99,0:55:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe, maybe not.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.16,0:55:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But your words are against the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.87,0:55:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.71,0:55:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And no one can protect you from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.40,0:56:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten months.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.98,0:56:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.57,0:56:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But your words are against the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.95,0:56:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Still no sign of this supposed insanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.83,0:56:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.04,0:56:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And no one can protect you from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.88,0:57:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can always have Jehovah’s words with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.18,0:57:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“Instruct me in your way, O Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.39,0:57:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not hand me over to my adversaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.48,0:57:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“for false witnesses have risen up against me,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.90,0:57:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they threaten me with violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.86,0:57:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“Where would I be if I did not have faith
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.53,0:57:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I would see Jehovah’s goodness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.66,0:57:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in the land of the living?”
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.99,0:57:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, test your servants for ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.41,0:58:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, you look healthier than the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.17,0:58:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Continue giving them the diet they’ve requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.96,0:58:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know your God,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.30,0:58:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but you’ve proven
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.43,0:58:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to be ten times better than any priest
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.72,0:58:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or conjurer I’ve met.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.35,0:58:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He had a dream,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.68,0:58:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and no one can tell him what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.95,0:58:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah answered your prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.33,0:58:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hope in Jehovah;
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.54,0:58:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“be courageous and strong of heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.67,0:58:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, hope in Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.22,0:58:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare a sacrifice to Bel.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.73,0:59:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.36,0:59:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,To the gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.95,0:59:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This city is the jewel of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.62,0:59:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the Ishtar Gate, the gardens,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.12,0:59:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the ziggurat so high
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.33,0:59:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it reaches the gods themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.63,0:59:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No one would question that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.34,0:59:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s odd that only twelve months ago
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.38,0:59:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one of your servants
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.43,0:59:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,dared to suggest that you’d go insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.88,0:59:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this not Babylon the Great
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.14,0:59:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that I myself have built for the royal house
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.89,0:59:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with my own strength and might
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.44,0:59:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the glory of my majesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.69,0:59:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“To you it is being said,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.24,0:59:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“O King Nebuchadnezzar,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.40,0:59:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘The kingdom has gone away from you,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.66,1:00:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and from mankind you are being driven away.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.08,1:00:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘With the beasts of the field your dwelling will be,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.41,1:00:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and you will be given vegetation
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.42,1:00:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘to eat just like bulls,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.92,1:00:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and seven times will pass over you,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.21,1:00:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘until you know that the Most High
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.88,1:00:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘is Ruler in the kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.97,1:00:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘of mankind and that he grants it
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.14,1:00:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to whomever he wants.’”
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.81,1:00:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Stop! Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.86,1:00:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.03,1:00:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.30,1:00:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you and your wise men
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.30,1:01:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,have failed consistently,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.09,1:01:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you claim Daniel to be a fraud?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.76,1:01:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a trick.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.06,1:01:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel conspired against your father.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.48,1:01:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A trick.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.06,1:01:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how did he make it happen?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.36,1:01:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything he has said has come true,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.49,1:01:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which is quite different from our history with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.61,1:01:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My father trusted you,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.61,1:01:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and I trusted you, and you were all wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.95,1:01:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Either you failed or Marduk did.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.95,1:01:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, . . .
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.12,1:02:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me:
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.37,1:02:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this God in the heavens, Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.24,1:02:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What a thrilling drama!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.87,1:02:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And there’s much more\Nto learn from the life of Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.62,1:02:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We will enjoy Part II\Nduring the final session of this convention.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.59,1:03:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Daniel, we encounter\Nsome who oppose and misrepresent us.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.63,1:03:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we prevent\Nour faith from being undermined?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.80,1:03:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Please pay close attention
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.18,1:03:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to Brother David Splane of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.18,1:03:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as he delivers the talk
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.48,1:03:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Put Up a Hard Fight for the Faith”!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.74,1:03:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Put up a hard fight for the faith”!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.78,1:03:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, those are the words of Jude,\Nthe half brother of Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.25,1:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s important to consider them\Nin their context.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.00,1:03:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.25,1:03:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Please turn to Jude 3,\Nand then leave your Bibles open
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.25,1:03:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because we’re going\Nto consider another verse in Jude,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.51,1:03:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and this will help us\Nto get the point that Jude was making.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.59,1:03:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At Jude 3,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.39,1:03:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he says:\N“Beloved ones,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.64,1:03:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“although I was making\Nevery effort to write you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.73,1:04:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“about the salvation we hold in common,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.40,1:04:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“I found it necessary to write you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.65,1:04:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to urge you to put up\Na hard fight for the faith.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.83,1:04:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Jude himself
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.20,1:04:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,had been “[putting] up\Na hard fight for the faith.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.92,1:04:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider this:\NJust three years earlier,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.71,1:04:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,his own fleshly brother James
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.63,1:04:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,was stoned to death\Nat the order of High Priest Ananias.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.55,1:04:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That was an open attack on God’s people,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.55,1:04:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and it must have been\Nvery painful to Jude and to others.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.77,1:04:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But here is something interesting:
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.52,1:04:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jude is not warning his brothers
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.31,1:04:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,about High Priest Ananias\Nor about persecution.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.19,1:04:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He has something else in mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.20,1:04:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a different type of attack,\Nand this is a sneaky one.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.12,1:04:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at verse 4,\Nand we’ll see why he wrote his letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.66,1:04:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice that the very first words are\N“my reason is.”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.42,1:05:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,‘So this is what I have in mind\Nwhen I’m writing you brothers.’
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.79,1:05:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“My reason is that certain men\Nhave slipped in among you
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.63,1:05:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who were long ago appointed\Nto this judgment by the Scriptures.”
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.35,1:05:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jude is talking about false brothers
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.56,1:05:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,who are presenting a real danger\Nto the congregations
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.44,1:05:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—in some ways,\Na greater danger than outright persecution.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.90,1:05:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you notice what Jude said\Nabout those false brothers?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.15,1:05:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They had “slipped in.”
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.91,1:05:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They were sneaky.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.91,1:05:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that was true back then,\Nand it’s true today, as we’ll see.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.25,1:05:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And, brothers, this is a very serious matter\Nthat we’re considering today.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.58,1:05:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of this:
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.59,1:05:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the Christian congregation\Nbrought down by persecution
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.96,1:05:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the second and third centuries?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.34,1:05:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.97,1:05:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was brought down by false brothers
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.55,1:05:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and apostate teachings.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.22,1:06:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the Devil can use an outright attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.35,1:06:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He can use persecution
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.85,1:06:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to batter the structure\Nof the Christian congregation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.69,1:06:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes he uses rot from within,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.61,1:06:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a subtle means to attack us.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.12,1:06:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever method he uses,\Nwe have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.08,1:06:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Our faith is involved,\Nand our faith is worth fighting for.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.33,1:06:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a gift from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.33,1:06:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to hold on to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.67,1:06:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a product of his holy spirit.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.46,1:06:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to put up\Na hard fight for our faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.09,1:06:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this talk,\Nwe’re not going to discuss persecution.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.64,1:06:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re going to discuss\Ntwo of the subtle means
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.97,1:06:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan uses to weaken our faith:
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.48,1:06:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,apostasy
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.56,1:06:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and negative reports\Nabout Jehovah’s Witnesses in the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.48,1:06:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So first, let’s talk about apostasy,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.65,1:06:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll call it spiritual poison.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.49,1:06:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, think about poison.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.49,1:07:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the best way to avoid being poisoned?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.54,1:07:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have to recognize poison\Nwhen we see it, and then avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.50,1:07:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same principle applies
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.54,1:07:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to teachings that could destroy our faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.55,1:07:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s not always easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.84,1:07:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not many of our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.97,1:07:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,would deliberately get involved\Nwith apostates,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.81,1:07:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but it could happen without our realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.56,1:07:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We receive letters at times\Nfrom brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.35,1:07:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,who are troubled by something\Nthey saw on a web page,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.69,1:07:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,an accusation, a rumor about the Society,\Nor about the organization.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.70,1:07:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the problem is,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.70,1:07:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they had no idea\Nthat apostates were behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.28,1:07:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s tricky\Nbecause the apostates don’t advertise,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.45,1:07:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are now on an apostate web page.”
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.37,1:07:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They often pose as sincere Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.17,1:07:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,who just have questions or concerns.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.80,1:07:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And some who aren’t really apostates
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.22,1:07:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,can cause just as much trouble\Nas the apostates do
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.01,1:08:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,by their negative talk and criticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.01,1:08:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, we need to be on the alert.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.06,1:08:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.48,1:08:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose that out of curiosity
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.98,1:08:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you get into a discussion forum\Nwith individuals
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.86,1:08:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who claim to be Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.90,1:08:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, maybe they are, maybe they aren’t.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.49,1:08:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t know.\NYou’ve never met them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.49,1:08:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And someone starts asking questions:
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.74,1:08:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“What did you think\Nof last month’s broadcast?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.66,1:08:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really find it encouraging?”
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.16,1:08:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or “Do you think the brothers\Nwho write Wa{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}tchtower  {\r}articles
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.00,1:08:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“are living in the real world?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.00,1:08:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they realize\Njust how hard it is out here.”
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.46,1:08:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then a few others join in\Nwith their own negative comments.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.93,1:08:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you don’t know\Nwhether these individuals are apostates
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.26,1:08:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or just brothers and sisters\Nwho are in serious spiritual trouble.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.10,1:08:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.10,1:08:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it make you feel?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.10,1:08:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When you leave the forum,\Ndo you feel upbuilt,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.82,1:08:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,determined to expand your ministry,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.36,1:08:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,more convinced than ever that Jehovah\Nhas an organization that you love
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.11,1:09:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and that you’re delighted to be a part of?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.12,1:09:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you feel honored\Nto be a part of that organization?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.37,1:09:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Or does the experience leave you sad,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.46,1:09:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,uneasy, uncomfortable?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.79,1:09:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, someone might say,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.84,1:09:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“I need to get involved in that forum\Nso that I can help those people.”
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.55,1:09:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They shouldn’t be together.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.80,1:09:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if they aren’t apostates,\Nthey’re not good for one another.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.18,1:09:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying in that forum to “help someone”
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.43,1:09:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is like holding his hand\Nwhile he drinks poison
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.85,1:09:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and then having some yourself\Nso that he doesn’t have to drink alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.77,1:09:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to follow the advice
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.82,1:09:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded at Romans 16:17.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.57,1:09:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now think about this imaginary forum\Nthat we just described
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.58,1:09:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in the light of Romans 16:17.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.25,1:09:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember,\Nthere are all kinds of negative talk
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.67,1:09:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,flying around in this forum;
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.67,1:09:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you don’t know who’s behind it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.71,1:09:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And here’s what it says at Romans 16:17:
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.26,1:10:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now I urge you, brothers,\Nto keep your eye
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.93,1:10:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“on those who create divisions
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.10,1:10:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“and causes for stumbling
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.31,1:10:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“contrary to the teaching\Nthat you have learned,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.73,1:10:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and avoid them.”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.73,1:10:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now think about that forum.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.32,1:10:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it create divisions?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.32,1:10:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.91,1:10:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a cause for stumbling?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.95,1:10:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.33,1:10:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it contrary to what we have learned?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.08,1:10:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we even have to answer that question?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.92,1:10:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, whether it’s intended or not,\Nthe effect will be to weaken our faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.71,1:10:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.80,1:10:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Paul tell us to do\Nhere at the end of verse 17?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.55,1:10:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: “Avoid them.”
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.47,1:10:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I’d like to say a kind word
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.56,1:10:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to some who may be involved\Nin discussion forums.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.10,1:10:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You may like to use this medium\Nto blow off steam, so to speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.15,1:10:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe there are\Nlittle things in the congregation
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.57,1:11:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that are happening\Nthat you wonder about
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.57,1:11:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or decisions the elders have made
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.74,1:11:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that you wonder about,\Nand so you write.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.74,1:11:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You get involved in the forum,\Nand you blow off steam,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.12,1:11:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and after that, you feel better.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.50,1:11:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about others in the forum?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.96,1:11:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How do they feel?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.96,1:11:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn’t you feel awful\Nif negative comments you made
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.34,1:11:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,were responsible\Nfor someone leaving the truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.38,1:11:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you wouldn’t want that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.80,1:11:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So please, please,\Nbe careful about what you say.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.64,1:11:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, another person might say:
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.64,1:11:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, I can see where those warnings\Nabout apostates apply to so-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.69,1:11:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“He’s weak,\Nbut don’t worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.73,1:11:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m spiritually strong.\NI can handle it.”
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.15,1:11:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s like a weight lifter thinking\Nthat he can drink a vial of poison
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.95,1:11:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and it won’t hurt him\Nbecause he’s so big and strong.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.37,1:11:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not so strong,\Nso spiritual, so intelligent
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.74,1:11:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can’t be affected\Nby the poison of apostate ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.83,1:12:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when might we feel pressured
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.38,1:12:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to read something\Nthat the apostates have written?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.97,1:12:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider this scenario:
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.05,1:12:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The unbelieving husband of your Bible student
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.93,1:12:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,sends his wife a link\Nto an apostate web page and says,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.68,1:12:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“Here, you better look at this\Nand see what you’re getting into.”
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.23,1:12:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, your student is concerned,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.23,1:12:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and she wants you to take a look\Nand tell her what you think.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.82,1:12:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s not an option.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.94,1:12:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul says: “Avoid them.”
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.03,1:12:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn’t mean reading apostate literature
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.24,1:12:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or searching social media\Nto see what they’re saying about us.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.70,1:12:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you say to your student?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.25,1:12:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say something like this:
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.00,1:12:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“I can imagine\Nthat this is very upsetting for you,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.59,1:12:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“and you certainly do need to know\Nwhat you’re getting into.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.97,1:12:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have a suggestion.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.55,1:12:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“We have nothing to hide.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.30,1:12:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“When you’re at the meetings,\Nlisten carefully
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.35,1:12:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“to what the brothers are saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.35,1:12:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“Watch how we interact with one another.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.14,1:13:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take note\Nof how the organization is financed.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.19,1:13:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“Get to know the elders and their wives.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.86,1:13:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“Introduce yourself to the circuit overseer\Nand his wife when they come.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.49,1:13:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“Visit world headquarters or the branch.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.53,1:13:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“I’ll come with you.\NI’ll help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.78,1:13:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I want you to get really acquainted\Nwith the organization.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.29,1:13:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“And if you do,\NI’m sure you’ll soon realize
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.96,1:13:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that what these people\Nare saying about us isn’t true.”
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.88,1:13:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe you can think of a better answer,\Nbut you get the idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.05,1:13:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a few drops of poison in a drink
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.76,1:13:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,are enough to cause serious harm.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.43,1:13:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And apostates\Noften mix a few truths with lies.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.52,1:13:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember Eliphaz,\None of Job’s false comforters?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.19,1:13:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of what he said was true.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.19,1:13:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn to Job 5:13.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.91,1:13:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Job chapter 5 (I’ll give you a moment)\Nand verse 13.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.41,1:13:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,See if what I read sounds familiar:
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.50,1:14:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“He catches the wise in their own cunning,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.09,1:14:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the plans of the shrewd\Nare thwarted.”
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.55,1:14:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“He catches the wise in their own cunning.”
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.76,1:14:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that sound familiar?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.76,1:14:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.93,1:14:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Paul said the very same thing\Nat 1 Corinthians 3:19.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.56,1:14:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, in the marginal reference,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.56,1:14:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we see (in the little {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}a{\r}  in the middle there)
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.36,1:14:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Corinthians 3:19.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.53,1:14:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul may even have been quoting Eliphaz.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.49,1:14:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was a truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.03,1:14:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But how did Jehovah feel\Nabout Eliphaz’s argument overall?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.41,1:14:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s turn to Job 42:7
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.96,1:14:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how Jehovah felt about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.50,1:14:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Job 42:7:
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.05,1:14:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“After Jehovah had spoken these words to Job,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.26,1:14:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah said to Eliphaz the Temanite:
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.22,1:15:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘My anger burns against you\Nand your two companions,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.19,1:15:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘for you have not spoken\Nthe truth about me
Dialogue: 0,1:15:05.02,1:15:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as my servant Job has.’”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.36,1:15:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A few grains of truth\Nwere mixed in with falsehoods,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.86,1:15:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and at least some of what Eliphaz said\Nwas inspired by the demons.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.24,1:15:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.79,1:15:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He admitted it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.24,1:15:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Job 4:15-17.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.46,1:15:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll give you a moment.\NThis is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.59,1:15:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At Job 4:15-17,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.01,1:15:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Eliphaz says:\N“A spirit passed over my face;
Dialogue: 0,1:15:39.43,1:15:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“the hair of my flesh bristled.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.85,1:15:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“It then stood still,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.85,1:15:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but I did not recognize its appearance.”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.52,1:15:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s stop there for a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.52,1:15:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“I did not recognize its appearance.”
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.36,1:15:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So he didn’t know whom he was talking to,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.41,1:16:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,just like someone in a discussion forum\Nmay not know whom he is talking to.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.91,1:16:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s continue; he says:
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.33,1:16:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“A form was in front of my eyes;\Nthere was a calm,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.96,1:16:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“and then I heard a voice:
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.84,1:16:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Can a mortal man\Nbe more righteous than God?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.80,1:16:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Can a man\Nbe cleaner than his own Maker?’”
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.97,1:16:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it surprise you\Nthat a demon would get involved
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.14,1:16:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the debate\Nbetween Job and the false comforters?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.43,1:16:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn’t.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.64,1:16:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This was no small debate.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.23,1:16:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a big issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.90,1:16:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan had challenged Jehovah\Nin the presence of all the angels
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.03,1:16:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that no man\Nwould keep his integrity under test.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.49,1:16:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That demon was using Eliphaz
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.16,1:16:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to demoralize Job and weaken his faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.74,1:16:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This was something that Job had to fight for,\Nand Job fought back.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.25,1:16:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Apostates are more active in some places\Nthan they are in others.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.13,1:16:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So if there’s a lot of apostate activity\Nin your area,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.30,1:16:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,people in the territory may be listening
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.34,1:17:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and they may challenge you\Nwhen you meet them in the ministry.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.60,1:17:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So how should you handle it?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.76,1:17:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t try to argue with the apostates;
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.14,1:17:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t read their comments.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.81,1:17:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask the elders\Nor other experienced publishers
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.48,1:17:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for suggestions\Non how to answer the householders.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.03,1:17:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how poisonous are apostate teachings?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.82,1:17:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s find out\Nas we watch the following video.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.66,1:17:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was in my 40’s, I was divorced,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.63,1:17:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I had three younger kids at home,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.50,1:17:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was working three jobs,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.80,1:17:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had drifted away from the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.01,1:17:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I had an acquaintance who was telling me
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.93,1:17:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was in a cult
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.68,1:17:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I needed to look
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.39,1:17:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at some information that he had.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.56,1:17:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was about 30 years old,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.61,1:17:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a fellow employee saw
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.82,1:17:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that I was one of Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.40,1:18:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and was trying to access jw.org.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.70,1:18:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me about someone\Nhe knew in another country
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.37,1:18:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,who could prove to me\Nthat Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.66,1:18:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,didn’t have the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.54,1:18:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That made me curious,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.54,1:18:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and little by little, I was persuaded to look
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.62,1:18:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,at apostate material.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.46,1:18:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born and raised in the truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.17,1:18:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,chose to dedicate myself to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.47,1:18:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,at the age of 16,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.26,1:18:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but I began to associate with people
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.01,1:18:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,who had either formerly been associated
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.26,1:18:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.27,1:18:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,or were very loosely associated\Nwith Jehovah and his organization,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.56,1:18:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s really where the apostasy\Nbegan to take root.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.86,1:18:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,As I was reading this literature,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.44,1:18:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw through it to an extent,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.86,1:18:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but when you’re drifting away,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.91,1:18:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re looking for a reason not to believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.08,1:18:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I began to feed my mind
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.96,1:18:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with different philosophies, different ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.04,1:18:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I even studied different religions.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.46,1:19:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, I told myself\Nthat I was doing that academically,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.26,1:19:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but it started to influence the way
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.55,1:19:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that I thought and felt about things.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.05,1:19:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, the elders reached out to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.35,1:19:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very combative with those brothers.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.52,1:19:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I even made the accusation\Nthat Noah’s ark was
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.69,1:19:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a fairy tale,\Nthat it was part of mythology.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.36,1:19:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Those apostate doubts that I was reading
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.36,1:19:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,kept going deeper and deeper into my heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.37,1:19:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I stopped reading the publications,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.41,1:19:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I stopped going to the meetings,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.83,1:19:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a result,\Nmy spiritual routine was dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.71,1:19:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought I’d try to find truth elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.25,1:19:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And I looked for something out there that was
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.25,1:19:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in accord with what I knew the Bible taught.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.05,1:19:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn’t find anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.26,1:19:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One Sunday morning,\NI rode by the Kingdom Hall,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.14,1:19:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said to myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.14,1:19:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Oh, they’re all in there\Nwaiting for Armageddon.’
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.93,1:19:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately when I thought that thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.48,1:19:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to myself:
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.10,1:19:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, at least they\Nfeel good about themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.61,1:20:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel?’
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.61,1:20:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer was I felt terrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.70,1:20:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, by skillful use of the Scriptures\Nand just reasoning with me,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.83,1:20:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders got me to realize
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.12,1:20:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that I had been ‘carried off’
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.12,1:20:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or that I had been ‘taken captive’\Nby human philosophy,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.50,1:20:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,by the deceptions
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.79,1:20:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and the empty reasoning of men.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.30,1:20:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually said a prayer;\NI supplicated Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.26,1:20:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would really show me\Nthe way to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.01,1:20:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And he took away
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.01,1:20:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,this feeling of emptiness,\Nspiritually speaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.23,1:20:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that a relationship with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.44,1:20:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s our most precious possession.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.57,1:20:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to get back.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.98,1:20:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to study the Bible with sincerity.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.49,1:20:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted it to affect my mind and my heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.62,1:20:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wanted it to effect\Nchange in my behavior.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.49,1:20:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now as I did that,\NI felt Jehovah blessing those efforts.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.41,1:21:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He began to help me\Nto rebuild that relationship with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.50,1:21:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I began to use Jehovah’s name.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.46,1:21:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking about Jehovah became a wonderful joy
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.51,1:21:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and a great pleasure to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.55,1:21:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the result was that my ministry\Nwas very productive.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.01,1:21:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s an amazing joy
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.01,1:21:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to help someone\Ncome to love Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.98,1:21:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just so happy
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.98,1:21:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to be back under Jehovah’s wings
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.44,1:21:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and have that peace of mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.98,1:21:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How loving Jehovah is!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.49,1:21:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to help us.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.90,1:21:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And what better helper could we have?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.53,1:21:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s the best in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.83,1:21:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s consider\Nthe second challenge we face:
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.87,1:21:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,negative reports\Nabout Jehovah’s Witnesses in the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.88,1:21:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here’s a good principle to follow
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.92,1:21:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,—Proverbs 14:15.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.88,1:21:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll give you a moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.38,1:21:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At Proverbs chapter 14
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.30,1:21:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and verse 15,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.22,1:22:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it says:\N“The naive person believes every word,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.23,1:22:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but the shrewd one ponders each step.”
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.65,1:22:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people believe everything\Nthey read in the newspaper or see on TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.24,1:22:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.87,1:22:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.70,1:22:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider this:\NNow, you’re working from door to door,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.00,1:22:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and you meet a householder who says:
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.00,1:22:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“You Jehovah’s Witnesses are terrible people.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.33,1:22:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You let your children die.\NYou don’t accept medical treatment.”
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.42,1:22:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you ask the householder,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.88,1:22:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you know\Nany Jehovah’s Witnesses personally?”
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.72,1:22:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“No.”
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.05,1:22:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then where did you get the idea\Nthat we let our children die
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.43,1:22:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and don’t accept medical treatment?”
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.06,1:22:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The householder says:\N“I have it on good authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.35,1:22:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I read it in the newspaper.”
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.27,1:22:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it’s in the newspaper,\Nit must be true, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.11,1:22:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.11,1:22:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember this:\NReporters have a deadline to meet,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.45,1:23:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and a reporter may not have the time\Nor the inclination to check the facts.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.41,1:23:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Or the reporter\Nmay have written a balanced article,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.54,1:23:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but then the editor changes it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.63,1:23:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the editor\Ndoesn’t like Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.26,1:23:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,or he’s been misinformed about us.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.17,1:23:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it’s bad enough if people in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.72,1:23:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,believe everything they read in the newspaper
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.01,1:23:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but, brothers, let’s not be among them.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.06,1:23:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s not be naive;\Nlet’s consider things carefully.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.52,1:23:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly, sometimes there’s a TV program\Nabout Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.44,1:23:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a few of these programs\Nare balanced and fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.03,1:23:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Many or, I daresay, most are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.83,1:23:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they’re not, you’ll often find\Nthat the producers started out
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.37,1:23:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,with a negative view of Jehovah’s Witnesses
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.54,1:23:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they looked for information\Nto support their prejudice.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.25,1:23:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So whom did they turn to?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.50,1:23:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Apostates and the clergy.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.67,1:23:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,From them,\Nthey got suggestions for people to interview.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.22,1:23:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know what those people would say.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.85,1:24:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,At the very last minute,\Nthey may ask the brothers for a comment
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.35,1:24:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,just to give an appearance of fairness,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.35,1:24:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but the program wasn’t designed to be fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.19,1:24:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was designed to be unfair.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.23,1:24:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was slanted against Jehovah’s Witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.07,1:24:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s be clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.24,1:24:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Some news organizations\Nare very conscientious about their reporting,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.33,1:24:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and they want to present\Nboth sides of an issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.54,1:24:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And where Jehovah’s Witnesses\Nare concerned,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.75,1:24:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,they do so at their cost.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.25,1:24:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If a newspaper publishes\Nanything positive about us,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.67,1:24:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the churches will push back.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.67,1:24:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Our parishioners are upset.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.42,1:24:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,‘They subscribe to your newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.22,1:24:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and they don’t like reading favorable things\Nabout Jehovah’s Witnesses.’
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.72,1:24:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The message:
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.18,1:24:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If it ever happens again,\Nyou’re going to lose subscribers.’
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.69,1:24:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this matter of Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.44,1:24:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,being the subject of malicious reports\Nisn’t new.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.19,1:24:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about the days of Queen Esther.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.91,1:25:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Wicked Haman brings a bad report\Nto King Ahasuerus.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.37,1:25:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,‘The Jews don’t obey our laws.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.45,1:25:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re a danger to society.’
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.04,1:25:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Ahasuerus check the facts?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.88,1:25:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he demand proof?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.92,1:25:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.17,1:25:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahasuerus is naive;
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.42,1:25:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,he allows himself to be taken in by Haman.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.30,1:25:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are\Na lot of modern-day Hamans today,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.31,1:25:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and they use similar tactics.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.39,1:25:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result,\Nsome government officials are taken in.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.23,1:25:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They believe the slanderous accusations\Nof the apostates.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.53,1:25:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if they just took the time\Nto check the facts,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.65,1:25:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,they’d see that they’re being lied to,\Nbut they don’t check the facts.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.12,1:25:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now again, it’s bad enough, brothers,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.79,1:25:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when government officials\Nare taken in by false reports,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.46,1:25:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so don’t you be taken in.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.04,1:25:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever heard the expression\N“trial by media”?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.43,1:26:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It works like this:\NSomeone is charged with a crime,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.85,1:26:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the case\Nis widely publicized in the media,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.68,1:26:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the media\Npresents the case in such a way
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.52,1:26:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that everyone who hears about it\Nthinks the man is guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.60,1:26:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course,\Nto avoid a lawsuit for slander or libel,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.19,1:26:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,these media reports\Nare very carefully worded,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.40,1:26:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and we need to understand\Nwhat the wording means.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.57,1:26:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a good principle to keep in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.57,1:26:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,—Job chapter 12
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.54,1:26:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and verse 11.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.58,1:26:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s amazing how many principles
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.92,1:26:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we can draw from the book of Job\Nfor this talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.42,1:26:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At Job 12:11,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.88,1:26:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,this is Job speaking and he says:
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.13,1:26:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“Does not the ear test out words
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.89,1:26:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as the tongue tastes food?”
Dialogue: 0,1:26:49.22,1:26:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“Does not the ear test out words?”
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.98,1:26:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.65,1:26:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean that if we learn that apostates\Nare going to be featured on a TV program,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.28,1:27:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we should watch it\Nto see if what they say is true?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.53,1:27:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.95,1:27:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It basically means\Nto consider the source of the words.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.33,1:27:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If they are the words of apostates,\Nwhy would we believe them?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.71,1:27:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, think of it this way:
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.88,1:27:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a bottle on your shelf\Nthat’s marked “poison.”
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.42,1:27:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need to open it up and take a swig\Nto see if it really is poison?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.93,1:27:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe what the label says.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.26,1:27:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for the purpose of this discussion,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.85,1:27:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s consider another way\Nwe can test out words
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.02,1:27:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,—and that is to pay attention\Nto what the words mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.85,1:27:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, we talked about media reports
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.27,1:27:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and how these are very often carefully worded
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.44,1:27:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to avoid a lawsuit.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.53,1:27:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So suppose a report indicates
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.86,1:27:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that someone has been charged with a crime
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.41,1:27:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or that he’s being investigated.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.74,1:27:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, you have two words:\Ncharged and investigated.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.37,1:27:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t mean he’s guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.17,1:28:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Or suppose that someone\Nis convicted and put in jail.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.71,1:28:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that would apply\Nto our young brothers in Korea, wouldn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.63,1:28:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They were convicted and jailed.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.76,1:28:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was their crime?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.76,1:28:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They refused to kill someone.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.64,1:28:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they do anything wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.60,1:28:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if someone is found guilty by man,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.19,1:28:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,as Jesus was,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.19,1:28:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn’t mean that he’s guilty\Nin the sight of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.40,1:28:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, brothers,\Nwe really have to think about these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:28.74,1:28:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We may read that a person\Nor an organization was sued
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.91,1:28:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and then settled out of court.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.66,1:28:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Does settling out of court\Nmean that they were guilty?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.67,1:28:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Not necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.71,1:28:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in this country and others,\Ncourt cases are often handled by a jury.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.38,1:28:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, who are on the jury?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.39,1:28:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinary citizens with no legal training.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.89,1:28:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But not only that,\Nthese ordinary citizens
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.97,1:28:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t always have access to all the facts
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.56,1:29:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because the judge and lawyers decide\Nwhich facts will be shared with the jury,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.15,1:29:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so it’s unlikely that the whole truth\Nwill ever come out in court.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.11,1:29:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, neither side probably wants\Nthe whole truth to come out in court.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.08,1:29:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, sometimes attorneys\Ndeliberately withhold information
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.41,1:29:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that would be prejudicial to their clients.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.12,1:29:22.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And, in addition, the juries\Nhave prejudices like everyone else,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.29,1:29:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and some of them\Njust can’t set their prejudices aside.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.72,1:29:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll tell you an actual experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.01,1:29:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Some time ago,\Na lawyer told me about a case he had.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.60,1:29:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a case\Nof medical malpractice by a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.94,1:29:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a jury.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.35,1:29:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And at trial, the doctor was clearly shown\Nto be in the wrong
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.78,1:29:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,but the jury didn’t give the patient a penny.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.28,1:29:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The lawyer was confused.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.99,1:29:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So after the trial,\Nhe approached two of the jurors and asked,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.12,1:29:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you don’t mind, tell me which part\Nof the testimony you didn’t believe.”
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.33,1:30:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The jurors replied:\N“Oh, we didn’t get that far.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.42,1:30:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“The doctor was cute,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.54,1:30:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and we didn’t want him\Nto have to pay anything.”
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.59,1:30:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,With deep thinkers like that,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.59,1:30:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,no wonder many lawyers\Ntry to settle their cases
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.34,1:30:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than bring them to a jury.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.81,1:30:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But someone will say:
Dialogue: 0,1:30:17.14,1:30:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“No, I don’t believe\Nin settling out of court.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.56,1:30:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in justice and truth.”
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.98,1:30:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So that brings up the question,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.02,1:30:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it wrong to settle a matter\Nbefore it goes to trial?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.53,1:30:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it Scriptural?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.53,1:30:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s let Jesus answer that question.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.86,1:30:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn to Matthew 5:25, 26.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.00,1:30:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s interesting\Nthat Jesus should mention this
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.38,1:30:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with all the important things\Nthat Jesus taught.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.97,1:30:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 5:25, 26:
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.97,1:30:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be quick to settle matters
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.56,1:31:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“with your legal opponent,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.73,1:31:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“while you are with him on the way there,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.60,1:31:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that somehow the opponent\Nmay not turn you over to the judge,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:08.44,1:31:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the judge to the court attendant,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.94,1:31:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“and you get thrown into prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.03,1:31:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“I say to you for a fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.03,1:31:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“you will certainly not come out of there
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.24,1:31:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,until you have paid over\Nyour last small coin.”
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.75,1:31:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.04,1:31:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about the Mosaic Law.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.13,1:31:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there any provision in the Mosaic Law
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.21,1:31:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to throw someone in jail\Nif he couldn’t pay a debt?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.01,1:31:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn’t the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.72,1:31:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If he couldn’t pay, he’d have to work it off
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.26,1:31:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or a family member would have to work it off.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.01,1:31:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Jesus talks about prison and a judge,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.85,1:31:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s obviously referring\Nto what a Gentile judge would do.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.61,1:31:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you couldn’t necessarily expect\Njustice from him.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.07,1:31:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why might he rule against our brother?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.49,1:31:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe he got paid\Nunder the table by the other party.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.03,1:31:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe he was prejudiced
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.03,1:32:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,against the race\Nor the religion of the other party.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.79,1:32:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now notice, Jesus didn’t say\Nthat the man should settle
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.88,1:32:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,only if he was guilty.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.17,1:32:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, brothers, let’s not be naive;
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.38,1:32:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t believe everything you read.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.01,1:32:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because an article\Nis called a news report
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.47,1:32:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn’t make it true,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:20.47,1:32:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and an editorial is someone’s opinion
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.47,1:32:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—and that someone may be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.73,1:32:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And TV producers\Nmay have their own agenda,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.40,1:32:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,prejudice, and viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.40,1:32:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do we say in conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:38.12,1:32:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Our faith is under attack,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.74,1:32:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have to fight.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.75,1:32:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah gives us\Nwhat we need to fight with.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.67,1:32:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things he gives us\Nis good associations.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.13,1:32:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan will try to lure us\Naway from good associations.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.17,1:32:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll try to weaken our faith
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.84,1:32:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,by getting us involved in bad associations\Nwithout our knowing it,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.72,1:33:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah provides\Ngood association in the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.27,1:33:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,These are people we know.\NThese are people we love.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.93,1:33:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,These are people\Nwho have our best interests at heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.94,1:33:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep in mind the principle we find\Nat Proverbs 13:20:
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.41,1:33:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one walking with the wise\Nwill become wise,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.08,1:33:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one who has dealings with the stupid\Nwill fare badly.”
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.71,1:33:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the members of your congregation;
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.09,1:33:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that they are wise;
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.09,1:33:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you know that they have\Nyour best interests at heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.01,1:33:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you get involved in a forum,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.30,1:33:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you might not know whether you’re walking\Nwith wise persons or not
Dialogue: 0,1:33:43.18,1:33:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—at least not at first.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.18,1:33:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So be careful.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.52,1:33:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If the conversation turns negative,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.27,1:33:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,get out.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.15,1:33:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is behind\Nthe twisted teachings of apostates.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.15,1:34:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He is “the father of the lie.”
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.16,1:34:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And those who lie\Nare doing exactly what their father does.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.95,1:34:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostates have nothing\Nto offer us, brothers.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.87,1:34:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All they have to offer is hate.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.87,1:34:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All they have to offer\Nis criticism and negative talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.25,1:34:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But, oh, how upbuilt we feel
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.92,1:34:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re with those who love Jehovah!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.47,1:34:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah provides us\Nwith good, wholesome associations.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:24.01,1:34:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He also provides us with his Word of truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.22,1:34:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and an accurate knowledge of the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.27,1:34:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is the best defense against apostasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.65,1:34:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Read the Bible every day and meditate on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.31,1:34:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay attention to the words;\Npay attention to what they mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.82,1:34:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Be like the Beroeans\Nreferred to at Acts chapter 17
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.82,1:34:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and verses 10 and 11.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.24,1:34:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.66,1:34:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Acts 17:10, 11:
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.58,1:34:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“Immediately by night the brothers\Nsent both Paul and Silas to Beroea.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.51,1:35:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“On arriving,\Nthey went into the synagogue of the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.80,1:35:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now these were more noble-minded\Nthan those in Thessalonica,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.68,1:35:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“for they accepted the word\Nwith the greatest eagerness of mind,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.52,1:35:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“carefully examining the Scriptures daily
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.23,1:35:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“[carefully examining the Scriptures daily]
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.98,1:35:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to see whether these things were so.”
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.69,1:35:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Paul compares the Beroeans\Nwith the Thessalonians.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.57,1:35:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we know about the Thessalonians?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.83,1:35:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn’t have YouTube in those days,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.20,1:35:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but at one point, the Thessalonians\Napparently heard a rumor
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.92,1:35:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that “the day of Jehovah” had arrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.75,1:35:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Who circulated the rumor?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.80,1:35:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,An apostate?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.09,1:35:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.17,1:35:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But maybe it was just someone\Nwho had heard the rumor
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.72,1:35:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and passed it on without checking it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.26,1:35:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever done that
Dialogue: 0,1:35:48.26,1:35:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,—passed on a report\Nwithout checking the facts?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.68,1:35:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think all of us have to admit
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.23,1:35:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’ve been guilty of that\Nat one time or another.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.23,1:36:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But now,\Nhow did the Thessalonians react?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.15,1:36:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They were alarmed.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.69,1:36:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They were “quickly shaken\Nfrom [their] reason.”
Dialogue: 0,1:36:04.57,1:36:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We mustn’t let that happen to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.07,1:36:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hear something,\Ncheck it out;
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.62,1:36:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t just circulate it;\Ndon’t just believe it;
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.00,1:36:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,check it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.12,1:36:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Colossians 2:6, 7
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.46,1:36:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,—the last scripture we’ll read\Nduring this talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.96,1:36:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here Paul explains how we can avoid
Dialogue: 0,1:36:21.96,1:36:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,being quickly shaken from our reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.67,1:36:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read this final scripture.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.05,1:36:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Colossians 2:6, 7:
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.39,1:36:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, just as you\Nhave accepted Christ Jesus the Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.23,1:36:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“go on walking in union with him
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.44,1:36:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“[you do that, and you’ll be walking\Nwith a wise one, certainly],
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.65,1:36:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“being rooted and built up in him
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.07,1:36:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“[and then notice this]\Nand being stabilized in the faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.49,1:36:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,just as you were taught.”
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.37,1:36:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re “stabilized in the faith,”\Nwe won’t be quickly shaken
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.58,1:37:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,by unfounded accusations\Nby apostates or the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:04.26,1:37:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,False rumors are often spread during wartime.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:09.22,1:37:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, this is war.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.22,1:37:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to put up a hard fight for the faith
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.31,1:37:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,as if our life depended on it
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.81,1:37:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,—because it does!
Dialogue: 0,1:37:21.61,1:37:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Brother Splane,\Nfor that insightful talk.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:26.74,1:37:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This session has helped us\Nto safeguard our faith and to act in faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.45,1:37:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we look\Nforward to in the next two sessions?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.71,1:37:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Scriptural theme is Matthew 21:21,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.50,1:37:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which says in part:
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.54,1:37:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you have faith . . . , it will happen.”
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.21,1:37:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The next session begins with a symposium
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.76,1:37:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,highlighting women of strong faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.93,1:37:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And we eagerly anticipate\Nthe public Bible discourse
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.39,1:37:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“Have Faith in the Good News.”
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.19,1:38:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s sing together song number 38,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.27,1:38:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which draws attention\Nto our source of power, Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.28,1:38:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This song is entitled\N“He Will Make You Strong.”
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.07,1:38:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,After the song,\Nyou may have your local concluding prayer.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.08,1:38:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, that’s song number 38.
